# MULTI EXPOSURE Choose how the camera combines shots to create a multiple exposure. !Multi Exposure Example | Option | Description | |--------|-------------| | **ON** | Adjust multiple exposure settings and record multiple exposures.
â€¢ **ADDITIVE**: The camera adds the exposures together. You may need to lower exposure compensation depending on the number of shots.
â€¢ **AVERAGE**: The camera automatically optimizes exposure for the final picture. The background in series shot without changing the composition will be optimally exposed.
â€¢ **BRIGHT**: The camera compares the exposures and chooses only the brightest pixel at each location. Colors may be mixed depending on their brightness and hue.
â€¢ **DARK**: The camera compares the exposures and chooses only the darkest pixel at each location. Colors may be mixed depending on their brightness and hue. | | **OFF** | Multiple exposure mode disabled. | > ðŸ’¡ **Note:** > The camera can combine up to nine exposures.
